column14: SPro ice mmt 12km U/S (highway dstance) of gauge. Due to excessive slush and depth profile in the vicinity of the gauge, winter measurements are conducted at this location. Unaccounted for inflow include to Hoole, Teeter and Mould creeks. A generous estimate of the flow in these creeks equates to about 1% of the flow at Lower Liard and are therfore ignored. Investigated far end of river to confirm insignificalt flow. Found large pile up of ice on RB side. Confirmed frozen to bed on RB. 10m of open flow on RB with no visible velocity. Deemed insignificant. Higgh confidence mmt @ Uncertainty: ISO method, 2-sigma value (1 x Uncertainty Value reported in *.xml File). @ HG2 is feeding stage.working DWL at sensor line. High ice freeze up. Turning point on ice ledge. Have concerns about diurnal stage trace as U/S and D/S stations do not show this type of trace. Further inestigation required. Sensor line vent is confirmed to be clear. Overlay of secondary sensors match giving more confidence to the stage trace. Depth of sensor at 12:50: DWL(9.726)- Offset(8.579) = 1.147m. Depth of HG2 at 12:50: DWL(9.726)- Offset(8.734) = 0.992m. Only one DWL taken due to distance between mmt section and gauging station. Used logger values for MGH. Mid-section

No QA/QC concerns. EXTRAP NOT CONDUCTED. High confidence measurement. Due to an excessive slush & depth profile in the vicinity of the gauge, winter measurements are conducted approximately 12km U/S (highway distance) of the gauge.
